news.title: Hong Kong regulator to investigate PwC auditing of China Evergrande Group
news.para: Heavily indebted Evergrande has become a symbol of the years-long crisis in China's property market, and last month its onshore unit was accused of a $78 billion revenue overstatement.

news.title: SHF urges Maharashtra to cut premium to 5% to make government land freehold
news.para: Chairman of State Housing Federation Suhas Patwardhan told TOI that they have been demanding a reduction in premium, but that the government has kept it at 10%.

news.title: NCLT dismisses buyers' challenge to Monarch Brookefields LLP's resolution plan
news.para: Despite the said homebuyers’ claim being admitted during the Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP), the resolution plan approved by the Committee of Creditors (CoC) granted them only 60% of their claim amount, with no entitlement to the apartment in question.

news.title: Noida's Trident Realty raises Rs 1,200 crore through sale of assets
news.para: The company plans to use the proceeds to strengthen its residential portfolio, as it has lined up projects worth ₹15,000 crore for launch in 2024-25.

news.title: HCC Rs 350 crore rights issue oversubscribed 2.5 times
news.para: ​The company, in a statement, said it has retained an amount of Rs 350 crore, corresponding to 100 per cent of the rights issue size, with the balance being refunded to investors.

news.title: Sundream Group to invest Rs 250 crore in Noida project
news.para: The newly-announced investment is over and above the first phase investment and the construction for the second phase has begun, according to a statement.

news.title: Yes Bank founder gets bail, walks out of jail after four years
news.para: ​​The property belonging to Avantha Realty Ltd (ARL) was already mortgaged for a loan taken by the company from Yes Bank. It was purchased for Rs 378 crore -- against the market value of Rs 685 crore -- by Bliss Abode Private Limited, run by Rana Kapoor's wife Bindu Kapoor, in 2017.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance eyes Rs 300 crore disbursements in Rajasthan in next 2-3 years
news.para: ​The Chennai-based company offers home loans, plot loans, home improvement and extension loans and loans against property. It had recently strengthened its presence in Western parts of the country.

news.title: Average long-term mortgage rate in USA climbs above 7% in March 2024
news.para: Sales of previously occupied U.S. homes fell 4.3% in March from the previous month to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 4.19 million, the National Association of Realtors said Thursday.

news.title: NBCC to set up shadow lender to help save over $100 million: Sources
news.para: The construction and real estate developer estimates the move will help it save $108 million in interest costs over the next two years, said the sources, who did not want to be named as the discussions are private.

news.title: Despite maintenance, elderly parents can evict children from property: Punjab & Haryana HC
news.para: Punjab and Haryana high court's ruling allows elderly parents receiving maintenance to still seek eviction of children from occupied property. Gurdev Kaur, a 90-year-old widow, fought for her rights against her son's neglect.

news.title: Families living in tilted buildings seek Kolkata civic body's help
news.para: The buildings—one four-storey standalone house and a five-storey apartment built in 1994 and another five-storey apartment buildings built in 2000—reportedly started tilting about two decades ago.

news.title: Godrej family begins formal division of conglomerate
news.para: The amicable separation is between two branches of the founding family with Adi Godrej and brother Nadir Godrej on one side and their cousins Jamshyd Godrej and Smita Godrej Crishna on the other. The latter two are brother and sister.

news.title: ED attaches FD worth Rs 113 crore of Supreme Construction's director
news.para: Tekchandani, an influential businessman close to many senior politicians and RSS functionaries, had contributed to the construction of a hospital in Nagpur.

news.title: Schindler expects new installations in China to decline by 10% in 2024
news.para: Although Chinese installations outpaced the rest of Asia-Pacific in both units and value in the first quarter, Schindler said weakness in the country's construction activity would likely weigh on future orders.

news.title: Home building permits in Germany drop by 18% in February 2024
news.para: Germany has been jolted by the most severe slump in the property sector in decades, Some 18,200 permits were issued, which is 4,100 fewer than a year earlier, the data showed, as the slump enters its third year.

news.title: China needs to solve real estate crisis as soon as possible: IMF chief
news.para: Gaspar said China's debt was increasing by about two percentage points of gross domestic product each year, but Chinese authorities had enough policy space and options to control deficits and debt.

news.title: Spain’s Santander to exit mortgage business & cut 500 jobs in Germany by 2026
news.para: After years of boom, mortgage lending slowed sharply in Germany after a rapid rise in interest rates to stamp out inflation caused potential homeowners to stay on the sidelines. Recent data have shown a stabilisation of the market.

news.title: Spain’s ACS expects net profit to reach upto $1.06 billion by 2026
news.para: ACS told investors on Wednesday during a capital markets day that its net profit should reach between 850 million and 1 billion euros ($905 million-$1.06 billion) by 2026, while it forecast revenues of 43 billion-48 billion euros by then.

news.title: Global economy set to lose $38 trillion every year till 2050 amid climate change: Study
news.para: Maximilian Kotz, a PIK scientist, said, "Our study finds that the global economy is committed to an average income loss of 19 per cent by 2049 due to past emissions. This corresponds to a 17 per cent reduction in global GDP."
